text.section:
A support enforcement agency of this State that is providing services to the plaintiff shall:
take all steps necessary to enable an appropriate tribunal in this State or another state to obtain jurisdiction over the defendant;
request an appropriate tribunal to set a date, time, and place for a hearing;
make a reasonable effort to obtain all relevant information, including information as to income and property of the parties;
within 2 days, exclusive of Saturdays, Sundays, and legal holidays, after receipt of notice in a record from an initiating, responding, or registering tribunal, send a copy of the notice to the plaintiff;
within 2 days, exclusive of Saturdays, Sundays, and legal holidays, after receipt of communication in a record from the defendant or the defendant's attorney, send a copy of the communication to the plaintiff; and
notify the plaintiff if jurisdiction over the defendant cannot be obtained.
